The paper deals with preference elicitation in multiagent systems, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves voting protocols and aggregation of preferences, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT). The complexity analysis and NP-completeness results suggest that the paper may also belong to the data structures and algorithms sub-category (cs.DS). The paper also discusses strategic manipulation by voters, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multiagent systems (cs.MA).
